    {
      "key": "the_lucky_marksman",
      "name": "The Lucky Marksman",
      "rarity": "very rare",
      "type": "weapon (revolver)",
      "desc": "*Hitting headshots is very hard. So I shoot a target the size of a coin instead*\n\nThis magic revolver has 1d4 charges (maximum of 4) and regains 1d4 expended charges daily at dawn. While attuned to this weapon, you possess a number of golden coins equal to the number of charges currently available.\n\n*Ricochet.* When you take the Attack action and make a ranged attack with this weapon, rather than attacking a creature normally you can expend 1 charge to toss one of the golden coins into the air at a point you can see within 30 feet of you. The coin occupies that space until the attack is resolved. Instead of targeting a creature, you make the attack roll against the coin (AC 20). The coin is a Tiny object.\n\nIf you hit the coin, choose a creature you can see within 30 feet of the coin as the original target of the attack. After determining that the coin is hit, flip a coin:\n- Heads: The bullet ricochets off of the coin and deals an extra 2d8 radiant damage\n- Tails: The bullet splits into two & ricochets into a second creature within 30ft of the coin. Make a new attack roll against that creature.\n\nBoth the Heads & Tails properties ignore half cover and three-quarters cover if the coin has a clear line of sight to the target.\nIf you critically hit the coin, the attack gains the benefits of both Heads and Tails.\n\nThe coin falls harmlessly to the ground immediately after the attack is resolved, and disappears after 1 minute.\n\n*Magic Reload.* When you use a Bonus Action to reload this weapon, six magical bullets appear in its chamber. These bullets vanish if removed manually.\n\nThe weapon otherwise uses the statistics of a revolver.",
